5|$|On 9 June 2010, Dickov {{signed a}} one-year {{contract}} with League One club <b>Oldham</b> Athletic to become player-manager following the departure of previous manager Dave Penney. It was Dickov's first attempt at managing and expected to be his last club as a player. His first competitive game as <b>Oldham</b> manager ended in a 2–1 victory at rivals Tranmere with Dale Stephens scoring both goals, Dickov also praised the travelling army of <b>Oldham</b> Fans. On 4 September 2010, he made his debut coming on as a second-half substitute against Bristol Rovers.|$|E
